Fig. 21
). Retinaculum with 3 + 3 teeth and with 1–4 setae arranged as 1 , 0–1 , 0–2 (Fig. 15 ). Anterior and posterior parts of furcal subcoxa respectively with 38–44 and 17–25 setae (
Fig. 16
). Manubrium anteriorly with 1 + 1 setae, posteriorly with about 57–68 setae. Dens anteriorly with 4 ( 1, 1 , 2 ) setae, posteriorly with 7–8 ( 2–3 , 1,1,1,1,1) setae. Mucro with 3 teeth. (
Figs 17, 18
). Length ratio of manubrium:dens:mucro as 7 –10.7:6.5–7.3: 1 .

